Dear Commissioner,

I am writing to request immediate attention to the area located between Walnut and Tonopah. This area has become increasingly neglected, with large amounts of trash accumulating and individuals experiencing homelessness living behind the bushes. The conditions have created safety concerns and diminished the quality of life for the residents in this neighborhood.

This is a growing community with new homes, and we believe we deserve to live in a clean and safe environment. The current state of this area does not reflect the standards our community strives for.

I respectfully ask that the city send a cleanup crew and consider implementing measures to maintain the area regularly. Addressing this issue will greatly improve safety, cleanliness, and the overall well-being of our neighborhood.

Thank you for your attention to this matter. I appreciate your help in ensuring our community remains a healthy and safe place to live.

I walk the park trails every day, twice a day with my 2 dogs.  There has been a drastic increase of the use of electric skate boards, e-bikes, e-motorcycles and e-scooters on the trails.  Some of these vehicles are traveling at extremely high speeds around pedestrians and pets.  I say extreme, probably in the range of 20 to 30 miles an hour, or faster.  My dogs have almost been struck a couple of times and yes they're on leashes.  This afternoon, I called out a male subject who flew past myself and my dogs at a dangerous speed.  He stopped started yelling at me and cussing at me for telling him to slow down.  He almost got physical, but I was able to talk him out of a physical altercation.  This e-vehicle and some gas operated motocycles use has really increased over the past few years.  Occasionally in the past I saw a few Police Officers on bikes patrolling the trails, non in the past couple of years.  I never see Park Ranges and don't know if they exsist.  My name is Keith Graves, Cell 720-289-0239.  After today incident I have become very frustrated.  I'd like to know if some enforcement of regulations can be done.
